 a gnomish vanishing device? An awsome item, I believe it has a few charges of an invis that lasts 10-20 minutes? It is also rechargable with a class 5 battery you can purchase, and you dont need tinkering skill to recharge it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cayleu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Small correction, mid-100's isnt even close to good enough, you need high-100's to have a chance, preferrably close to 200. If you still doubt the incredible difficulty in getting a gnome to make one of these for you, look at this<BR> <A HREF="http://pub7.ezboard.com/ffulcrumstinkeringforumsworkbench.showMessage?topicID=517.topic" TARGET=_blank>http://pub7.ezboard.com/ffulcrumstinkeringforumsworkbench.showMessage?topicID=517.topic</A> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just a minor addition:<P>The diamond is not the problem. Diamonds are easy to come by compared to the real problem ingredient.<P>A haze panther eye.<P>Haze panthers are in Wakening lands and they drop eyes so rarely you'd think they were all genetically blind.<P>I got unbelievably lucky one day and got one from a panther that had agro'd on me as I was going by. I rounded up the other ingredients and a well known tinker on our server (Thank you Meshugugget!) put it together for me and I gave her a few hundred platinum for her time and effort. (and some white chocolate cookies if I recall)<P>Given the cost of the mana batteries, it's no cheaper than potions, but mana batteries stack, and it's a neat item to have.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The most cruel bit is the haze panther eyes are stackable. :P  Like anyone will have 30 in their possession.<P>I have two haze panther eyes sitting in my bank waiting for diamonds.<P>There is a casting time to GVD.  And like others said it's about as expensive as just buying potions.  Potions are instant cast.  But for the sake of inventory space and convenience (haven't found a potion vendor in Kael, I'm kos in Thurgadin), one of these would make my life easier.  The batteries are stackable, 5 charges each.  So that's 100 invis'es per inventory slot in the bank.  (Deluxe toolbox is 10-slot also, so it's not a burden to store it unless you're crammed for space)<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wyvern G</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Haze Panther eyes are the bane of my existence.  To kill them I log onto a 60 druid friend, very hard for a cleric to solo in a zone like WL.<P>Haze panthers dont root well at all, so the snare really helps kill them, good luck with your panthers, Ive killed about 35 and 0 eyes.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
